                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13493147" author="anchela" created="Thu, 8 Nov 2012 12:50:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;this is a bug not an improvement....&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13493148" author="anchela" created="Thu, 8 Nov 2012 12:52:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;... and it blocks any kind of access control implementation work.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13500950" author="alex.parvulescu" created="Tue, 20 Nov 2012 09:53:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;proposed patch.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I took a simple approach by adding an optional property &quot;declaringNodeTypes&quot; which if defined will be compared against the indexed node type.&lt;br/&gt;
The declaringNodeTypes addition isn&apos;t hierarchy aware with regards to node types. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Not declaring this property should fallback to previous behavior.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13503236" author="alex.parvulescu" created="Fri, 23 Nov 2012 16:07:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;following &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-470&quot; title=&quot;Documentation for the PropertyIndex&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;OAK-470&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;OAK-470&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, I&apos;ve updated the patch.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;feedback welcome&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13561519" author="alex.parvulescu" created="Thu, 24 Jan 2013 09:20:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Updated patch to apply against the Property2Index which is the new default index impl.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13564178" author="alex.parvulescu" created="Mon, 28 Jan 2013 10:24:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;pushed the initial patch with rev 1439331.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;if this proves insufficient, we&apos;ll track other improvements separately.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
